text:
What Indian nationalists are trying to do is totally absurd. When you boycott products and services from a specific country, you have to make sure that it will hurt the other side, so much so that they will be forced to change their behavior.

When you look at the figures, all is clear and such a boycott decision is foolish and childish. Here are the facts. 

1) The trade volume between Turkiye and India is about 8 billion USD, Turkiye imports from India is around 5.2 billion USD while India's imports from Turkiye is about 2.8 billion USD. So, India has a trade surplus of 2.4 billion USD against Turkiye. So, it is actually India who will be a net loser if they attempt to use trade as a weapon. When we look at the big picture, the share of Turkiye's export to India is about 1% of its total exports, which is nothing. 

2) Some Indians foolishly believe that they can affect Turkiye's tourism revenues. That is even beyond absurd. Turkiye is one of the biggest tourist destinations in the world (top 5 in the world). In 2024, the country attracted about 65 million tourists. Indian tourists constitute not even 0.4% of the total. Also, last year Turkiye's tourism revenue was about 61 billion USD. The revenue from Indian tourists don't make up even 0.3% of the total. To put thing in perspective, only Istanbul attracts twice the number of tourists whole India gets in a year. Also, city of Antalya is visited by more tourists than whole India. Long and short of it, the effect of Indian tourists on Turkiye's tourism industry is akin to a fly on an elephant.

In summary, Indian nationalists are out of touch with reality, and they have a completely distorted view of their country's strength in global affairs.

Indeed, the West operates with a morally strategic agenda, and we all recognize this reality. The pressing question is, what actions will you take in response? The videos disseminated by you and your dawah group are pathetic; they merely depict us as desperate victims seeking the mercy of those who do not share our beliefs. If your London-based dawah group persists with this ineffective approach, you risk cultivating a generation of victims‚Äîone that believes Palestine can be redeemed through the international courts of tawagheet and the United Nations of kufr. 

It's time to stop lamenting how the US and other states of kufr are playing unfairly. They have always operated under these principles, as the Quran has warned us. Ali Dawah, I trust that deep down, you and your followers understand what the youth truly need to hear. We are on the brink of an inevitable conflict between iman and kufr, and your current approach to dawah is not equipping the youth with the necessary tools for this struggle. 

No adult Muslim male today should occupy himself with endeavors that wont put him at odds with the authorities of kufr. My brothers, I urge you to reflect on the scholars who faced imprisonment or execution, and consider the reasons behind their fates. You will quickly identify a recurring pattern: certain topics, if addressed, often result in severe consequences. Ironically, these are precisely the subjects that the ummah urgently needs to confront, and this is the challenge that Allah has set before our daees.
